Let $p(x) = ax + b$. We have:

\begin{align*}
p(2) &= a(2) + b = 2 \\
p(3) &= a(3) + b = 3
\end{align*}

Solving this system of linear equations, we get:

\begin{align*}
a &= \frac{1}{2} \\
b &= \frac{1}{2}
\end{align*}

So, $p(x) = \frac{1}{2}x + \frac{1}{2}$.

Therefore, $p(x) + q(x) = \frac{1}{2}x + \frac{1}{2} + \frac{x}{(x-1)x} = \boxed{\frac{x+2}{2(x-1)}}$.

